-- Shanghai Zendai, Forte, Greentown to Form $147 Million Property Venture
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-04-27T14:25:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-27/shanghai-zendai-forte-greentown-to-form-147-million-property-venture.html

          
          
             Shanghai Zendai Property Ltd. said
it is setting up a 1 billion yuan ($147 million) venture in
Shanghai with Shanghai Forte Land Co., a Greentown China
Holdings Ltd. unit and Shanghai Panshi Investment Management Co.  
 Zendai will hold 50 percent of the new company, which will
have registered capital of 1 billion yuan, and will provide a
loan of 1 billion yuan to the venture, it said in a statement to
the Hong Kong stock exchange today.  
 Shanghai Forte, which holds 19.47 percent of Shanghai
Zendai, will take a 30 percent stake in the venture and will
provide a loan of 2.57 billion yuan, subject to conditions,
according to the statement.  
 Shanghai Zendai said it sees great potential for property
development and investment in Shanghai and the venture will
allow the companies to pool funds for larger projects.  
 Shares of Shanghai Zendai and Shanghai Forte, which were
suspended in Hong Kong yesterday, will resume trading tomorrow,
the companies said in statements. Shanghai Forte fell 3.2
percent on April 23 while Shanghai Zendai dropped 5.3 percent.  
